MNTC 413 (W 3 – 0 – 0 3.0)
COURSE DESCRIPTION1
This course presents a comprehensive overview of the principal components of surface
mine design. Topics include pit limit analysis and economic optimization, haul road design,
blast design, and basic stability calculations. Equipment selection and application and mine
scheduling techniques will be introduced, including dragline applications. Application of
surface mining operations will be classified with case studies. The focus will be on the
practical application of design techniques to mine planning, and on the available
equipment and methods for field monitoring to provide effective design feedback and
support safe operations.
Prerequisites: MNTC 305 (Introduction to Mining), MNTC 310 (Mining and Society)
PRE-REQUISITE KNOWLEDGE
This course is designed for learners with little to no knowledge or experience in mineral
economics.
